textBeforeTable: Career Statistics (Regular Season) Game Log Stats Read more   International: Made his first appearance for Sierra Leone in August 2013 for a World Cup qualifier against Equatorial Guinea. Was also called-up for African Cup of Nations qualifying in 2014. Personal: Born in Freetown, Sierra Leone, Lahoud moved to the Washington, D.C. area with his family at the age of three. College: A four-year starter at Wake Forest, Lahoud led the Demon Deacons to the 2007 NCAA National Championship and finished his career with 14 goals and 20 assists. 2009: Drafted by Chivas USA in the first round (ninth overall) of the 2009 SuperDraft.  He appeared in 16 games, starting nine and logging 872 minutes.   He also started both of Chivas USA’s MLS Cup Playoff games. 2010: He made 23 appearances for the club, including 20 starts, logging 1684 minutes.  2011: Lahoud made 23 appearances for the club, including 17 starts, logging 1341 minutes. He scored his second career goal on June 18 against FC Dallas. 2012: Midfielder Michael Lahoud
